    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-navy-800 mb-3 mt-6">Contractor Payment Delays</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Government and corporate contracts often pay on milestone basis—Net-30, Net-60, sometimes Net-90 days after work completion. During this gap, your business still operates. Employees need wages. Materials need purchasing. Equipment needs fuel.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Business capital financing with 0% down payment preserves cash to bridge these payment gaps. You have working capital available while waiting for contract payments.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-navy-800 mb-3 mt-6">Seasonal Cash Flow Variations</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Malaysian SMEs face seasonal fluctuations. Construction slows during monsoon. Retail peaks during festive seasons. Tourism fluctuates with school holidays.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Traditional bank loans don't account for this—fixed monthly payments regardless of revenue. Flexible financing structures align payments with your business cycles.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-navy-800 mb-3 mt-6">Equipment Age Restrictions</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Banks typically won't finance equipment older than 5-10 years. But for many SMEs, well-maintained used equipment is the sensible choice—40-60% cheaper than new, still plenty of useful life remaining.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Private equipment financing often has no age restrictions. A 7-year-old Komatsu excavator in good condition can be financed, allowing you to acquire productive equipment at a fraction of new equipment cost.
    </p>

